headline: McDonald’s expects low-income Americans to spend less amid US slowdown
summary: McDonald’s expects price-sensitive Americans to cut back further as a slowing US economy, sticky inflation and higher fast-food prices squeeze household budgets. While the burger chain’s quarterly results showed rising global sales, executives warned that low-income consumers are reducing visits and spending less per order, signalling a tougher backdrop for the wider quick-service restaurant (QSR)…

headline: McDonald’s (MCD) Profit Margin Holds at 32.2%, but Slower Earnings Growth Tests Bullish Narratives
summary: McDonald's (MCD) reported steady earnings with 1% growth for the year, which is a bit softer than its robust 9.9% average annual growth over the past five years. The company's net profit margin came in at a strong 32.2%, just below last year's 32.3%. Analysts see earnings growing 6.8% per year ahead, which is behind broader U.S. market expectations. With attractive dividends, continued profitability, and limited headline risks, the latest results highlight both the brand's resilience and the...
